General FAQ

This document is a community driven full breakdown of the respective class. This is a live document where we actively change it based on feedback and changes to the game to provide the best information to the community. The majority of us hang around in the Community Lost Ark Discord in our respective class channels. If you would like to give us feedback or ask questions contact us there.

Why should I play this class?

Artillerist is a versatile class with a mix of damage, stagger, destruction and survivability. It has many skill options that let you adjust to any situation and is overall fun to play. Barrage, the wheelchair, lets you facetank many patterns while dishing out big damage, while Firepower lets you be nimble and constantly drop big nukes on your target.

How does my identity work?

Firepower Meter

Barrage Meter

The Firepower gauge, on the left, gives you a buff that increases as you fill up this bar, up to 30% more damage.

The meter will stay full while you deal damage, but will start depleting if you don't hit anything for more than 8 seconds.

The three different levels of buff can be seen in the gauge, level 1, 2 and 3 with the colors being white, yellow and red.

The Firepower Enhancement engraving extends how long the meter takes to deplete and

On the right, the Barrage gauge allows you to enter wheelchair mode, replacing your skills, giving you a 20% damage reduction buff and push-immunity.

Exiting this mode gives you a Cooling Effect debuff that prevents you from gaining gauge for a certain amount of time.

This meter does not deplete.

The Barrage Enhancement engraving disables this debuff, letting you rebuild this meter as soon as you exit.

How do I decide on a build?

Both have their strengths and weaknesses. It’s a matter of personal preference.

Here’s a short summary of the builds. For further information, read their respective sections of this document.

What are my Party Synergies?

Synergies are a buff your party benefits from. These only apply to your party and not the entire raid. Consistent synergies are up for most of the fight while Burst synergies are much more infrequent.

Why is Yearning important?

It’s considered a part of a build despite not being on your character.

Swamp of Yearning is used by supports and gives +8/10/12% Damage and Attack/Move speed to the party. This is a Relic Set they use that has a golden ring.

FAQ: Barrage Enhancement

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Is All-Out Attack mandatory?

No, but it’s highly recommended due to the Quality of Life that comes with it, along with reducing the build cost and making you hit your wheelchair abilities more easily.

Can I replace Adrenaline?

No, the other version of the guide had all the math and I cannot be bothered, just trust me on this, you need the crit.

Can I replace KBW?

No, same thing as above, your wheelchair has 40% crit from the engraving so you get insane benefit from KBW during it.

Are there Specialization Breakpoints?

This question splits into 2 parts:

For 4 Wealths, 9 skill rotations, no

As long as you're above roughly 1600 spec, if you hit the 9 skills as described in the rotations section, you should be ready to go.

For 5 Wealth, 8 skill rotation, yes

It mainly comes down to Gravity Explosion(GE) and Summon Turret hits

Specialization

GE Hold Duration

Attacks by one turret

1807

1.1s

2

1647-1806

1.1s

3

1646

1.4s

2

With more than 1 turret active, you no longer have breakpoints.

Attack speed buffs can help turret attack faster and get you ready for wheelchair faster

Best advice is try it in Trixion and see what works smoothly for you at your gems and specialization

How do I decide if I want Crit or Swift?

Basically, Crit is more damage and more expensive, and requires more care when playing as it's slower.

Swift is cheaper and more nimble and can be more fun for some, but at the cost of damage.

If you care about sheer performance only, go Spec Crit
If you want a budget alt with more comfort, go Spec Swift

Does Barrage scale with levels?

Yes, Wheelchair mode gets stronger at levels 55 and 60.

Firepower Enhancement

Written by Punkrr

Playstyle

Firepower Enhancement does away with Barrage Mode and just focuses on dropping good ol’ nukes on your target. It's low pressure, easy to maintain and agile.

The builds center around balancing good cooldown reduction and crit rate, as uptime is very important for FPE.

Stat Allocation

Firepower Artillerist is a Crit/Swift based class with the split being flexible, however the most effective distributions are Full Crit with 1 Swift Ring / Earring or Full Swift

Crit

The Crit variants of FPE are the burstiest variant of the class but will have high cooldowns, the higher your CD gems are, the better this variant will feel to play. This build will have the most damage in a single rotation, making it better for older content or raids with very high group DPS.
70/30 is recommended for both crit variants, can optionally use earring (60/40) instead, if frequently playing with a crit synergy or bracelet with precise

  • Nightmare Crit will be the burstiest and most frontloaded damage possible, the downside being over longer fights the DPS will get lower due to Boundless/Magick Addiction upkeep.

  • Hallucination Crit has a higher DPS over longer fights while still being burstier than the Swiftness variants. This build is expected to get the most value out of Elixirs that are yet to come to our version in the West. This build is currently only recommended if you have trouble managing Magick Addiction/Boundless on the standard Nightmare Crit build.

The Swift build has 2 variants, 6 Nightmare (Boundless) and 2 Nightmare / 4 Dominion (2nm4dom), both builds will offer a much faster experience, with more utility than the Crit build.

  • The Boundless variant offers the lowest cooldowns but lowest DPS (5-10% Loss). The playstyle is very high APM which can be a positive or a negative for some players.
  • The 2nm4dom variant has very high DPS over longer damage windows, however in raids where you get low uptime the burstier crit options are likely to perform better. This build is not recommended until Ancient tier accessories, as it requires both very high swiftness (1800+) and 5x3+1 Awakening to maintain Dominion Fangs buff without Conviction/Judgment (Artillerist doesn’t have great options for these runes currently).

Gear Set

Nightmare is the primary damage set for both stat variants. Full Swift focuses on maintaining the Boundless state for maximum spam.

Hallucination is used as an alternative Crit option with Adrenaline 1.


2 Nightmare / 4 Dominion Fang is an alternative option to the Full Swift Boundless build with similar performance that is relatively easier to maintain the Dominion buff as opposed to maintaining Boundless.

FAQ: Firepower Enhancement

Questions sourced from frequent interactions within the Unofficial Lost Ark Discord

Can I replace Adrenaline?

No.

Hit Master or Cursed Doll?

Hit Master doesn’t affect Bleed rune, any kind of burn DoTs, nor awakening damage.
However the damage difference is negligible due to Cursed Doll being additive to Adrenaline (and Ether Predator), meaning it also loses out on about 1% of its 16% damage.
Choose whichever you can afford, though Cursed Doll does have a non-negligible downside making your potions heal you for less.

Should I use Barrage Mode as FPE?

Not for damage.
Without spec it does very poor damage period.
However, it can be used for lots of utility: when entering Barrage Mode you get 20% total DR (as opposed to with the FPE engraving), Push Immunity, access to a 30% shield, and more Destruction skills.

Can Firepower invest into Spec?

It ramps up the cost of the build and loses you Swiftness, making it a more expensive, slower playstyle, at which point you might as well play Barrage

If you wish to invest into Crit Spec Firepower, basically swap Swift for Spec and run Salvation with Gravity Explosion as your 8th skill.

Should I stay in Boundless Mana or what?

You will not be able to maintain boundless unless you're full Swift, where it is beneficial, and even then it's hard to maintain. There is nothing inherently wrong in dipping into boundless with other ratios of Swift, it's not a major damage loss, so overall don't micromanage it.

Should I use Conviction/Judgment?

It's a personal choice, most people don't want to micromanage it, but if you're down for that it will help you stay in Magick Addiction and the CDR will help with damage over time.
Currently Artillerist’s skill/tripod options for these runes aren’t the most consistent without giving up damage or utility

Make sure to avoid running it completely on the Boundless variant, as it will make it harder to upkeep.
